{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Velocitone ReaScripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A collection of ReaScripts for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.reaper.fm/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
REAPER
}}}
 that provide track tagging, tag-based filtering, color management, toolbar syncing, and hardware controller integration.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Prerequisites\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.reaper.fm/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
REAPER
}}}
 (v6+)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
 \u8212- REAPER's package manager\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.sws-extension.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
SWS Extension
}}}
 \u8212- recommended (required for startup action and some script features)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=212174"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
js_ReaScriptAPI
}}}
 \u8212- required for Track Manager filtering scripts\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Install via ReaPack\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab In REAPER, go to {\b Extensions > ReaPack > Import repositories...}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Paste this URL:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 https://github.com/chrislundeen/Velocitone-ReaScripts/raw/main/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Go to {\b Extensions > ReaPack > Browse packages}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Search for "Velocitone" and install the scripts you want\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Restart REAPER\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Set Up the Startup Script\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The startup script keeps the toolbar tag sync running in the background. To enable it:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Option A \u8212- SWS Startup Action (recommended):}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Go to {\b Actions > Show action list}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for {\f1 Velocitone: Startup ReaScript}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Right-click the action \u8594 ? {\b Copy selected action command ID}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Go to {\b Extensions > Startup actions > Set global startup action}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Paste the command ID and confirm\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Option B \u8212- Built-in {\f1 __startup.lua}:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Create a file called {\f1 __startup.lua} in your REAPER {\f1 Scripts/} folder with this one line:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 dofile(reaper.GetResourcePath() .. '/Scripts/Velocitone-ReaScripts/Velocitone - startup.lua')\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 REAPER automatically runs any {\f1 __startup.lua} on launch.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Track Tag Manager\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A system for organizing tracks by tagging their names with labels like {\f1 [audio]}, {\f1 [buss]}, {\f1 [midi]}, {\f1 [fx]}, etc.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Tag Track Name} scripts toggle a tag at the end of the selected track's name. Run the action once to add the tag, run it again to remove it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Available tags: {\f1 [audio]}, {\f1 [buss]}, {\f1 [channelstrip]}, {\f1 [custom]}, {\f1 [folder]}, {\f1 [fx]}, {\f1 [gfx]} (guitar FX), {\f1 [midi]}, {\f1 [output]}, {\f1 [section]}, {\f1 [stem]}, {\f1 [tape]}, {\f1 [vsti]}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Example: A track named {\f1 Drums} becomes {\f1 Drums [audio]}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Tag-Based Track Filtering\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Tag Filter} scripts control track visibility based on tags. Activate a filter to show only tracks with that tag \u8212- useful for managing large sessions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each Tag Filter action acts as a toggle (on/off) and reports its state to REAPER's toolbar button system\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Reset Tag Filter} clears all active filters, making all tracks visible again\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Filters work through REAPER's Track Manager window (requires js_ReaScriptAPI)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Track Color Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Color Gradient for Child Tracks} \u8212- Applies a smooth color gradient across a parent track's children, interpolating brightness and saturation based on nesting depth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Color Media Items Variation of Parent Track Color} \u8212- Colors selected media items with randomized shade variations of their top-level parent track's color\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Track Name Tools\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Track Name Character Replacement} \u8212- Prompts for a search string and replacement, then performs find-and-replace on all selected track names\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 MCP Track Selection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Navigate the Mixer Control Panel (MCP) with dedicated actions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Select Visible MCP Track - Next} \u8212- Selects the next visible track in the mixer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Select Visible MCP Track - Previous} \u8212- Selects the previous visible track in the mixer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Select Visible MCP Track - Controller} \u8212- Reads encoder direction from hardware input (-1 = previous, +1 = next) for use with MIDI controllers\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Toolbar Sync\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The startup script runs a background loop that keeps REAPER toolbar buttons in sync with the current tag filter and track tag states. This means toolbar buttons reflect whether a tag filter is active or which tags are applied \u8212- providing visual feedback through button states (off/hover/on).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Hardware Control \u8212- MIDIFighter Twister\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Four scripts for switching banks on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.midifighter.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
DJ TechTools MIDIFighter Twister
}}}
 controller:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Select Bank 1\u8211-4} \u8212- Switches the Twister to the specified bank\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Library Files\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Scripts under {\f1 _library/} are internal modules loaded by the user-facing scripts above. They do {\b not} appear in REAPER's Actions list and are not meant to be run directly.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Toolbar Icons\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These scripts are designed to work with the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/chrislundeen/velocitone-reaper-toolbar-Icons"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Velocitone REAPER Toolbar Icons
}}}
 repository, which provides matching multi-state toolbar icons and track icons.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The icon repo generates icons that correspond to the tag system (audio, buss, midi, fx, guitar, etc.) with three visual states \u8212- off, hover, and on \u8212- that align with the toolbar sync behavior of these scripts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Icons are installed to:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 REAPER/Data/toolbar_icons/} \u8212- toolbar button icons (with 150% and 200% HiDPI variants)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 REAPER/Data/track_icons/Custom/} \u8212- track icons for REAPER's track icon feature\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 See the toolbar icons repository for setup instructions.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
}
